/========== Known Issues ==========\
16 April 2025 -- I'm hitting component number limits with the game files. While I now have fighter/bomber combo hangars so the AI doesn't just build fighters only AND I have fighter-only hangars so players can add in those for space superiority (combo hangars force a 50/50 fighter/bomber split) right now I am NOT able to add in bomber-only hangars b/c I've run out of components to use. For now all that is in the game are combo fighter/bomber hangars and fighter-only hangars.




/========== Installation ==========\
1. Download the .zip or .7z archive for DWUR that holds all of the mod's files
2. Create a directory for the mod within your Distant Worlds: Universe folder's CUSTOMIZATION directory...you can call this whatever you'd like.
3. Unpack the downloaded DWUR archive into the directory you created in step 2. IF YOU EXPAND FILES DIRECTLY INTO THE CUSTOMIZATION FOLDER, THE GAME WON'T KNOW WHAT TO DO WITH THEM.
4. Launch the game.
5. Go to "Change Theme"
6. Pick the name of the directory you created in step 2 and click Activate Theme.

(The game might hang for up to a minute while everything loads)

7. Exit the game and restart (even though the game loads the files after clicking "Activate Theme", it only partially loads...I don't know why DW:U is like this...I'm not a developer :D You need to exit the game and restart after activating the theme.)
8. You'll know the mod is fully activated by seeing the custom DWUR background and hearing the music (if you have your music volume turned on)
9. Enjoy!